                    <tei:idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/2822</tei:idno>
                    <tei:note type="abstract" source="bib2822-1">Rabban Sliba (father of Rabban Joshua) was a monastic author who composed a martyrology in the late thirteenth century or early fourteenth century (some time after the death of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/239">Bar ʿEbroyo</persName>. One source describes him as being from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/217">Ḥaḥ</placeName>.</tei:note>
